Tag your bungee partner 🙈🇳🇿 Jumping over the Waikato River in New Zealand! Bungee jumping is an activity that involves a person jumping from a great height while connected to a large elastic cord. The launching pad is usually erected on a tall structure such as a building or crane, a bridge across a deep ravine, or on a natural geographic feature such as a cliff

📽 @_daniharris #nature
📍 Taupō, New Zealand

node.text:
Caption this for us! 😅🦊 Curious Fox filmed by @marius.birkeland83 introduces himself to @jens.birkeland in Lofoten, Norway.

Lofoten is an archipelago in Norway. Its known for its dramatic scenery, with peaks like the Svolværgeita pinnacle jutting up into the sky. Himmeltindan Mountain sits on Vestvågøya Island. The nearby Lofotr Viking Museum features a Viking longhouse reconstruction. Cycle routes cover the islands, passing through fishing villages like Henningsvær, which has colorful buildings lining its waterways.

📽 @marius.birkeland83 w/ @jens.birkeland #nature
📍Vesterålen, Lofoten, Norway

node.text:
Diving headfirst into the weekend like… ☁️ Wingsuit flying (or wingsuiting) is the sport of flying through the air using a wingsuit which adds surface area to the human body to enable a significant increase in lift. 

This wingsuit flight was shot in Montserrat Natural Park, a multi-peaked mountain range near Barcelona, in Catalonia, Spain.

"Montserrat" literally means "serrated (like the common handsaw) mountain" in Catalan. It describes its peculiar aspect with a multitude of rock formations that are visible from a great distance. The mountain is composed of strikingly pink conglomerate, a form of sedimentary rock.

📽 @daniroman_ @fredfugen @vincent.cotte @bras.noir #nature
📍Montserrant, Spain

node.text:
Would you drive this? 😅 This footage was taken in Borneo, the third-largest island in the world and the largest in Asia. Immerse in the Southeast Asia’s Malay Archipelago, is shared by the Malaysian states of Sabah and Sarawak, Indonesian Kalimantan and the tiny nation of Brunei. It’s known for its beaches and ancient, biodiverse rainforest, home to wildlife including orangutans and clouded leopards. In Sabah is 4,095m-tall Mount Kinabalu, the island’s highest peak, and, offshore, the famed dive site Sipadan Island.

📽 @khaiiidiir #nature
📍 Kalimantan, Indonesia
🎶 JayCal PR - Me Llamaste

Yoga and Meditation with Guru Turtle via @jacintashackleton 🧘🏼‍♂️This unique type of meditation is all about relaxation and being one with the ocean 🌿😄

The Great Barrier Reef in the Australian estate of Queensland is home to six out of seven of the world's sea turtle species. Not only this coast is radiant with sunshine, but its picturesque landscapes are also overflowing with an impressive population of native animals.

From witnessing baby turtles make their way to the sea to see adult turtles enjoying @nature, that's a magical sight to behold.

Tag your @nature lovers friends! 🐢

📽 @jacintashackleton #nature
📍 Queensland, Australia
🎶 Arnaud Gauthier - Yoga

node.text:
Hiking adventures in Norway 🥾

Bondhusvatnet glacier lake near Sundal in Kvinnherad is a popular destination and one of the most famous hikes in the Norwegian Hardanger region. The colors of the lake, the unique landscape, and the glacier in the background make Bondhusdalen one of the most beautiful valleys in Norway.

Who would you share a hike here with? 🇳🇴

📽 @natezeth #nature
📍 Bondhusvatnet, Norway
🎶 James Bay - Wild Love

node.text:
The best leg ever 🐶🦵Tag someone who has to see this!

Cancano (1907 meters above sea level) is one of the most visited and photographed places in Alta Valtellina. Located in “Val Fraele” (Fraele valley), in the Lombardy region of Italy, it has been a protected area included in the borders of the Stelvio National Park since 1977.

About 15 kilometres from Bormio, the Cancano lakes area surprises its visitors thanks to the majesty of its environment where the 2 big artificial basins of Cancano and San Giacomo stand out from the scenery.

📽 @pusateriandrea #nature
📍Cancano Lake, Italy
🎶 Tommee Profitt - In The End (Mellen Gi Remix) [feat. Fleurie]

node.text:
Is this the most beautiful mantis in @nature? Flower mantises are those species of praying mantises that mimic flowers. Their coloration is an example of aggressive mimicry, a form of camouflage in which a predator's colours and patterns lure prey.

📽 @insecthaus_adi #nature

node.text:
The biggest animal on Earth via @adam_ernster. 🐋 Blue Whales can hold their breath for about 90 minutes, reaching a maximum length of 100 feet or 30 metres long and weight up to 200 tons, it is the largest animal known to have ever existed... 🤯

This video was taken in the Santa Barbara Channel where over 27 different types of whales and dolphins call this place home, making these waters one of the best whale watching areas in the world.

From May to September you can see Blue Whales, Minke Whales and Humpback Whales. Occasionally, you can see Right Whales or Orcas. All season long you have an excellent chance of seeing dolphins, porpoises, seals and sea lions.

Who would you share this experience with? 🐳

📽 @condorexpresssb & @adam_ernster
📍 Santa Barbara, California, USA
🎶 Thomas Newman - Wow
